10
00:01:59.920 --> 00:02:01.110
<i>- Hello?</i>

11
00:02:01.110 --> 00:02:03.670
Where are you? Why weren't you answering your phone?

12
00:02:03.670 --> 00:02:06.220
Just now I was out of cell range.

13
00:02:08.040 --> 00:02:10.190
I think I'll get to the village entrance in a minute.

14
00:02:10.190 --> 00:02:12.120
Alright. I'll wait for you at the village entrance.

15
00:02:12.120 --> 00:02:13.630
Okay.

16
00:02:25.080 --> 00:02:28.190
Chang has gotten access to the files of Red Coast.

17
00:02:31.740 --> 00:02:35.360
Do you know the purpose of Red Coast Base?

18
00:02:39.080 --> 00:02:41.710
To search for extraterrestrial intelligence.

19
00:02:41.710 --> 00:02:44.840
Simply put, to look for aliens.

20
00:02:44.840 --> 00:02:46.470
You knew it?

21
00:02:46.470 --> 00:02:48.150
Yeah.

22
00:02:50.520 --> 00:02:54.750
Chang has shared this information with other Combat Zones.

23
00:02:54.750 --> 00:02:57.460
He also pulled their files about their search

24
00:02:57.460 --> 00:03:00.420
for extraterrestrial intelligence in recent years.

25
00:03:01.340 --> 00:03:03.190
Where's Ye Wenjie?

26
00:03:03.190 --> 00:03:06.560
She said she wanted to stay here for a while, reminisce about the past,

27
00:03:06.560 --> 00:03:09.350
and visit her old friends while she's at it.

28
00:03:10.590 --> 00:03:15.570
The old lady's surprisingly poised. What about her relations with Shen Yufei?

29
00:03:15.570 --> 00:03:19.360
According to Qi Jianguo, they didn't have many dealings.

30
00:03:19.360 --> 00:03:20.680
And her red ginseng?

31
00:03:20.680 --> 00:03:22.630
That was a gift from the villagers.

32
00:03:22.630 --> 00:03:25.430
Professor Ye has nothing to do with the red ginseng factory.

33
00:03:25.430 --> 00:03:28.240
What about you? Did you find anything about the factory?

34
00:03:29.520 --> 00:03:32.520
Shen Yufei's just an adviser working for the foreign company.

35
00:03:32.520 --> 00:03:36.860
She periodically comes here to check the fruits of development before acceptance.

36
00:03:36.860 --> 00:03:39.000
She seems to be in a hurry. She's already left.

37
00:03:39.000 --> 00:03:41.080
Outwardly, there's nothing suspicious.

38
00:03:41.080 --> 00:03:42.970
But I don't believe it.

39
00:03:42.970 --> 00:03:45.740
I don't believe it's so coincidental.

40
00:03:45.740 --> 00:03:49.260
But I have no way to arrest her or interrogate her.

41
00:03:51.800 --> 00:03:53.310
Let's go.

42
00:03:53.310 --> 00:03:55.510
Where to?

43
00:03:55.510 --> 00:03:58.360
Home. To do some research about Red Coast.

44
00:04:13.220 --> 00:04:14.680
Can we have some rest first?

45
00:04:14.680 --> 00:04:17.510
Is it possible to have them send that chopper here to pick us up?

46
00:04:17.510 --> 00:04:20.000
Do I look like a chopper to you?

47
00:04:33.870 --> 00:04:38.700
Just now you said Ye Wenjie wanted to visit some old friends.

48
00:04:40.000 --> 00:04:41.360
What kind of old friends?

49
00:04:41.360 --> 00:04:45.100
Given that she lived here for so many years. She probably has a lot of friends.

50
00:04:47.480 --> 00:04:49.480
Old friends.

51
00:05:15.430 --> 00:05:17.920
In your description,

52
00:05:17.920 --> 00:05:24.780
Red Coast was made of harsh cold steel.

53
00:05:25.360 --> 00:05:30.410
I always thought this place was a forest of concrete.

54
00:05:30.410 --> 00:05:34.730
But the sight of it makes me feel

55
00:05:36.310 --> 00:05:39.180
it has something warm about it.

56
00:05:40.430 --> 00:05:45.700
That's because it's abandoned.

57
00:05:46.230 --> 00:05:48.190
It's old.

58
00:05:49.920 --> 00:05:57.100
Anything that has lost its power
and is dying

59
00:05:58.190 --> 00:06:01.340
tends not to put people on the defensive.

60
00:06:07.240 --> 00:06:10.540
I feel like a pilgrim here.

61
00:06:11.510 --> 00:06:17.730
Like a believer who finally made it to Jerusalem.

62
00:06:19.630 --> 00:06:23.840
This is where it all started.

63
00:06:24.430 --> 00:06:30.170
As the Buddha puts it, it's predestined bonding.

64
00:06:35.970 --> 00:06:39.190
Long time no see, Commander.

65
00:06:41.040 --> 00:06:44.030
You don't have to call me that.

66
00:06:47.560 --> 00:06:50.920
The Commander's status is untouchable.

67
00:06:50.920 --> 00:06:57.770
To me, to ETO, you're our spiritual leader.

68
00:06:57.770 --> 00:07:01.580
You'll always be the supreme commander of ETO.

69
00:07:04.190 --> 00:07:07.620
When I was all alone in this world,

70
00:07:07.620 --> 00:07:11.120
with nowhere to find any spiritual assistance,

71
00:07:11.120 --> 00:07:14.360
when I was even too helpless to understand the meaning of life,

72
00:07:14.360 --> 00:07:18.000
even the meaning of despair was beyond me.

73
00:07:18.000 --> 00:07:20.800
Whenever such greatness appeared,

74
00:07:20.800 --> 00:07:24.390
I saw how small and despicable we were,

75
00:07:25.560 --> 00:07:29.610
that lives were worthy of respect and sacrifice,

76
00:07:30.560 --> 00:07:32.820
that everything changed.

77
00:07:32.820 --> 00:07:36.720
Then a door opened, and a new road appeared.

78
00:07:40.390 --> 00:07:44.870
You were the one who lit that lamp, Commander.

79
00:07:49.430 --> 00:07:53.680
Only you pushed

80
00:07:53.680 --> 00:07:57.000
the button to contact Lord.

81
00:07:57.870 --> 00:08:03.260
Pushing a button is just an insignificant movement.

82
00:08:04.430 --> 00:08:10.160
Many major changes in human history were triggered by an insignificant movement.

83
00:08:10.160 --> 00:08:15.500
Stefan Zweig even picked some stories and made a book out of them.

84
00:08:15.500 --> 00:08:19.380
Decisive Moments in History.

85
00:08:19.380 --> 00:08:22.260
But they're different from you.

86
00:08:23.230 --> 00:08:27.660
You didn't do it by accident.

87
00:08:29.920 --> 00:08:33.030
You made a choice.

88
00:08:33.030 --> 00:08:36.870
Even the achievements of all outstanding humans combined

89
00:08:36.870 --> 00:08:42.030
stand no comparison with the great decision you made.

90
00:08:42.540 --> 00:08:46.410
What really established a communication mechanism with Lord

91
00:08:49.570 --> 00:08:52.350
was your Second Red Coast.

92
00:08:56.360 --> 00:08:59.540
It's our Second Red Coast.

93
00:08:59.540 --> 00:09:03.720
(19 years ago)

94
00:09:29.790 --> 00:09:32.520
You named it the Second Red Coast?

95
00:09:32.520 --> 00:09:34.240
Yeah.

96
00:09:34.240 --> 00:09:37.150
Red Coast is a great name.

97
00:09:38.480 --> 00:09:40.170
What is this place?

98
00:09:40.170 --> 00:09:42.450
Judgment Day.

99
00:09:42.450 --> 00:09:44.030
Three years ago,

100
00:09:44.030 --> 00:09:47.740
you gave me the direction and frequency required for contacting Lord.

101
00:09:47.740 --> 00:09:51.170
Otherwise the Second Red Coast would never have been built.

102
00:09:53.940 --> 00:09:56.850
Contacting Lord will take a long time.

103
00:09:58.510 --> 00:10:00.440
Yeah.

104
00:10:00.440 --> 00:10:04.110
Our lives are too short.

105
00:10:04.720 --> 00:10:09.930
Fortunately, you gave me and ETO a chance.

106
00:10:13.200 --> 00:10:17.270
Commander, if you didn't choose me,

107
00:10:17.270 --> 00:10:21.100
I would never be able to communicate with Lord.

108
00:10:22.870 --> 00:10:27.960
At that time, in front of the first batch of ETO members,

109
00:10:27.960 --> 00:10:33.080
you said our ideal was to invite Lord to reform human civilization,

110
00:10:33.080 --> 00:10:37.860
to curb human madness and evilness, so that

111
00:10:37.860 --> 00:10:44.150
the Earth can once again become a harmonious, prosperous, sinless world.

112
00:10:45.080 --> 00:10:46.650
Yeah.

113
00:10:46.650 --> 00:10:52.100
But now everything has changed.

114
00:10:53.160 --> 00:10:55.000
You disagree with me,

115
00:10:55.000 --> 00:10:59.360
because you haven't seen the true colors of mankind.

116
00:11:07.480 --> 00:11:11.150
Everything you did was based on love.

117
00:11:11.150 --> 00:11:12.790
You love mankind.

118
00:11:12.790 --> 00:11:14.940
You love the earth.

119
00:11:15.670 --> 00:11:21.100
Even becoming the Commander was your move to keep ETO from losing control.

120
00:11:21.100 --> 00:11:25.450
There's too little I can do.

121
00:11:27.240 --> 00:11:29.510
I looked into you.

122
00:11:29.510 --> 00:11:33.160
I even read your father's books.

123
00:11:33.650 --> 00:11:39.520
I found that in this aspect, you're greatly influenced by your father.

124
00:11:39.520 --> 00:11:45.040
Because of your great sense of responsibility, no matter how much harm you suffer,

125
00:11:45.040 --> 00:11:48.950
you'll never give up the last bit of hope.

126
00:11:48.950 --> 00:11:52.670
You can't bear to part from the splendid human civilization,

127
00:11:52.670 --> 00:12:00.850
but has it ever occurred to you that the evil of humanity is imperishable?

128
00:12:00.850 --> 00:12:06.610
Even I, your very first follower, has betrayed you.

129
00:12:07.360 --> 00:12:12.130
Commander, humans are absolutely incorrigible.

130
00:12:14.580 --> 00:12:16.510
Actually,

131
00:12:17.090 --> 00:12:19.530
you didn't have to come here to see me.

132
00:12:20.480 --> 00:12:24.740
I know you're still trying to get information about Lord.

133
00:12:24.740 --> 00:12:27.840
You even rebuilt the reception system.

134
00:12:27.840 --> 00:12:29.440
It's right here.

135
00:12:29.440 --> 00:12:33.960
This used to be the great Red Coast.

136
00:12:34.750 --> 00:12:37.550
I never thought you'd build a new Red Coast

137
00:12:37.550 --> 00:12:40.770
on the ruins of the abandoned one.

138
00:12:41.450 --> 00:12:46.240
I think we should call it the Third Red Coast.

139
00:12:51.120 --> 00:12:56.120
Did you change the reception and transmission methods?

140
00:12:56.120 --> 00:12:59.820
Or have you been fabricating it this whole time?

141
00:13:02.600 --> 00:13:05.240
Lord is coming.

142
00:13:05.240 --> 00:13:08.130
Who am I to fabricate that?

143
00:13:09.770 --> 00:13:15.200
I think it's merciful to let humans destroy themselves.

144
00:13:15.200 --> 00:13:17.840
Only humans will be destroyed.

145
00:13:17.840 --> 00:13:22.270
This world will be changed.

146
00:13:23.240 --> 00:13:25.250
Commander,

147
00:13:26.210 --> 00:13:31.130
has there ever been any mercy in the history of human civilization?

148
00:13:33.410 --> 00:13:38.590
Evans, you still have a choice.

149
00:13:42.250 --> 00:13:47.840
Compared with the universe, anything is insignificant.

150
00:13:47.840 --> 00:13:51.320
I don't want to make any pointless choices.

151
00:13:52.960 --> 00:13:59.430
Humans are trapped in an inferno, unable to get out.

152
00:14:00.010 --> 00:14:06.320
And you were the one who started the fire.

153
00:14:09.120 --> 00:14:12.660
Thank you, Commander.

154
00:14:32.000 --> 00:14:34.170
I started the fire,

155
00:14:37.510 --> 00:14:39.990
but I can't keep it under control.

156
00:14:49.000 --> 00:14:53.670
According to the archives, the Red Coast Base was built in 1968,

157
00:14:53.670 --> 00:14:56.030
and abandoned in 1987.

158
00:14:56.030 --> 00:14:57.720
During the 20 years of its service,

159
00:14:57.720 --> 00:15:00.870
no abnormal radio wave from the space was detected.

160
00:15:00.870 --> 00:15:03.480
So they didn't find any aliens.

161
00:15:03.480 --> 00:15:05.340
For now, that's one way to put it.

162
00:15:05.340 --> 00:15:06.510
For now?

163
00:15:06.510 --> 00:15:08.060
Yeah.

164
00:15:08.580 --> 00:15:10.510
Because the universe is vast,

165
00:15:10.510 --> 00:15:12.910
and there are many kinds of interference in it,

166
00:15:12.910 --> 00:15:16.750
which makes the traveling speed of the radio wave seem very slow.

167
00:15:16.750 --> 00:15:19.750
And the longer the distance, the weaker the signal.

168
00:15:19.750 --> 00:15:25.080
But we can't say for sure no aliens have received our radio waves.

169
00:15:25.080 --> 00:15:27.120
There are so many archives here.

170
00:15:27.120 --> 00:15:31.480
Are there any details that don't tally with Ye Wenjie's words?

171
00:15:31.480 --> 00:15:35.550
What Professor Ye told me was mainly about the true purpose of Red Coast.

172
00:15:35.550 --> 00:15:39.030
It accords with the archives almost perfectly.

173
00:15:39.030 --> 00:15:41.550
If at that time the whole world was looking for aliens,

174
00:15:41.550 --> 00:15:45.860
was it really necessary to make it that confidential?

175
00:15:46.370 --> 00:15:48.670
I asked Professor Ye the same question.

176
00:15:48.670 --> 00:15:51.080
She gave me an explanation.

177
00:15:51.080 --> 00:15:54.380
There's some information about it in the archives as well.

178
00:15:54.380 --> 00:15:58.670
Have you guys ever heard of Bill Mathers's "contact as symbol" theory?

179
00:15:58.670 --> 00:15:59.870
What?

180
00:15:59.870 --> 00:16:01.080
What? What? What?

181
00:16:01.080 --> 00:16:02.820
I'll put it in a simple way.

182
00:16:02.820 --> 00:16:08.090
It means contact with an alien civilization is only a symbol or a switch.

183
00:16:08.090 --> 00:16:12.200
Regardless of the content of the encounter, the results would be the same.

184
00:16:12.200 --> 00:16:17.000
The impact would be magnified by the lens of human mass psychology and culture

185
00:16:17.000 --> 00:16:21.850
until it resulted in huge, substantive influences on the progress of civilization.

186
00:16:21.850 --> 00:16:24.910
If such contact were monopolized by one country

187
00:16:24.910 --> 00:16:26.790
or political force, the significance would be comparable

188
00:16:26.790 --> 00:16:31.220
to an overwhelming advantage in economic and military power.

189
00:16:35.080 --> 00:16:36.320
You can't understand?

190
00:16:36.320 --> 00:16:37.550
It's not that.

191
00:16:37.550 --> 00:16:40.750
Actually, what you said was not difficult to understand.

192
00:16:40.750 --> 00:16:43.810
It's just that your wording and your way of speakingâ€¦ Iâ€¦

193
00:16:43.810 --> 00:16:48.050
It means making contact with an alien civilization is like getting a book about superb martial arts.

194
00:16:48.050 --> 00:16:52.480
Whoever gets it and learns the skills will become invincible.

195
00:16:52.480 --> 00:16:55.240
Captain Shi, that's what you mean, right?

196
00:16:55.240 --> 00:16:58.270
That's exactly what I mean. Clear and easy to understand.

197
00:16:58.270 --> 00:17:00.390
- Professor Wang, you made it sound complicated.
- It's my bad.

198
00:17:00.390 --> 00:17:03.240
It's like all martial artists are fighting for a martial arts book,

199
00:17:03.240 --> 00:17:05.400
throwing the martial arts world into chaos.

200
00:17:05.400 --> 00:17:10.740
If you're right, once anybody gets in touch with aliens, the world will be changed.

201
00:17:10.740 --> 00:17:14.780
Chang also said those foreign terrorists used to be pacifists.

202
00:17:14.780 --> 00:17:16.500
There're also those scientists who committed suicide.

203
00:17:16.500 --> 00:17:18.790
They all changed without warning.

204
00:17:18.790 --> 00:17:23.920
Was it because they made contact with aliens?

205
00:17:23.920 --> 00:17:30.580
Professor Ye also said the search for alien civilization is a very special subject.

206
00:17:30.580 --> 00:17:34.250
It has a strong influence on the researchers' outlook on life.

207
00:17:34.960 --> 00:17:37.020
Professor Ye. 
 <i>[Astrophysicist]</i>

208
00:17:37.020 --> 00:17:41.240
Professor Ye is indeed quite special.

209
00:17:42.820 --> 00:17:47.030
Xu Bingbing, did the ten of you find anything else?

210
00:17:48.000 --> 00:17:52.160
Overall, the infosheets about Red Coast correspond with Professor Wang's words,

211
00:17:52.160 --> 00:17:56.200
but I don't know if you've noticed these details.

212
00:17:56.200 --> 00:18:00.100
Yang Weining and Ye Wenjie registered their marriage in 1973.

213
00:18:04.860 --> 00:18:06.160
(Personnel Who Died in Line of Duty)
And here.

