Oct 21, 1979)

215
00:18:09.940 --> 00:18:13.270
(Mountaintop platform Dropped to his death)

216
00:18:13.270 --> 00:18:15.270
Lei Zhicheng

217
00:18:15.270 --> 00:18:20.730
and Ye Wenjie's husband Yang Weining both died in the Red Coast?

218
00:18:20.730 --> 00:18:22.790
On the same day.

219
00:18:31.200 --> 00:18:32.720
Professor Ye.

220
00:18:32.720 --> 00:18:37.490
Professor Ye is way too special.

221
00:18:41.660 --> 00:18:43.590
(Astrophysicist, Ye Wenjie)

222
00:18:43.590 --> 00:18:48.810
I know your research and study about alien civilization are state secrets of your countries.

223
00:18:48.810 --> 00:18:54.590
I'm very grateful to you for sharing them to let us analyze them together.

224
00:18:54.590 --> 00:18:59.070
Unfortunately, none of our searches have been turned to any results.

225
00:18:59.070 --> 00:19:01.830
The signals from space are just static.

226
00:19:01.830 --> 00:19:04.510
It's just the natural noises of the planets.

227
00:19:04.510 --> 00:19:07.000
This is why we cannot accept it call.

228
00:19:07.000 --> 00:19:10.830
That's what we can call the miracle from another civilization.

229
00:19:10.830 --> 00:19:13.400
The original conjectures of the Global Battle Command Center

230
00:19:13.400 --> 00:19:16.590
also include the possibility it was aliens' doing,

231
00:19:16.590 --> 00:19:20.240
but this is what we're most unwilling to admit.

232
00:19:20.240 --> 00:19:27.640
If they are indeed alien civilization from outer space, how do we respond?

233
00:19:27.640 --> 00:19:29.240
We're not prepared for that.

234
00:19:29.240 --> 00:19:31.110
To this space civilization,

235
00:19:31.110 --> 00:19:34.100
we're like 16th-century aboriginal Americans,

236
00:19:34.100 --> 00:19:38.480
watching the Spanish armada come over the horizon.

237
00:19:38.480 --> 00:19:41.210
There's nothing we can do.

238
00:19:50.590 --> 00:19:53.350
I've still got so many Red Coast infosheets to read. Why did you bring me so many more?

239
00:19:53.350 --> 00:19:54.880
Do you want me to look into nanotech or not?

240
00:19:54.880 --> 00:19:58.030
You need to do both, and do them well.

241
00:19:58.030 --> 00:19:59.960
Xu Bingbing sifted out these infosheets.

242
00:19:59.960 --> 00:20:03.540
Red Coast didn't find any aliens. See if any other countries did.

243
00:20:04.440 --> 00:20:07.200
After reading these infosheets, I found there were indeed a couple of occasions

244
00:20:07.200 --> 00:20:10.110
when the radio frequencies were abnormal.

245
00:20:10.110 --> 00:20:11.880
Abnormal how?

246
00:20:12.960 --> 00:20:15.070
But it's absolutely impossible.

247
00:20:15.070 --> 00:20:16.960
Look, take this one for example.

248
00:20:16.960 --> 00:20:18.680
It's too far away from us.

249
00:20:18.680 --> 00:20:22.280
If it was really aliens trying to contact us, a round trip would take them billions of years.

250
00:20:22.280 --> 00:20:23.960
There's no telling if the earth would still be there by that time.

251
00:20:23.960 --> 00:20:26.590
Is it possible they can travel really fast?

252
00:20:26.590 --> 00:20:28.160
Just like those in the movies.

253
00:20:28.160 --> 00:20:29.590
Faster than light.

254
00:20:29.590 --> 00:20:33.200
If they could travel at light speed, why would they send radio signals?

255
00:20:33.200 --> 00:20:35.020
Just like you. You got a cellphone.

