284
00:21:56.680 --> 00:21:59.960
Only Professor Ye knows if that's necessary.

285
00:21:59.960 --> 00:22:02.000
If they made no discoveries whatsoever,

286
00:22:02.000 --> 00:22:06.960
then how come these oddities led us to the subject of alien civilization?

287
00:22:06.960 --> 00:22:10.070
Why didn't they tell us the Black and White Death Envoys were real?

288
00:22:10.780 --> 00:22:11.880
Is it really that important?

289
00:22:11.880 --> 00:22:13.480
It is.

290
00:22:13.480 --> 00:22:15.590
It's very important.

291
00:22:23.680 --> 00:22:28.540
Lately, I've read many famous astronomy books.

292
00:22:29.400 --> 00:22:32.830
I find that the Fermi paradox is really pretty interesting.

293
00:22:32.830 --> 00:22:36.550
It's such a big universe. How can we be alone?

294
00:22:36.550 --> 00:22:40.370
But if there are aliens, where are they?

295
00:22:42.240 --> 00:22:45.130
When the Fermi paradox was first developed,

296
00:22:45.130 --> 00:22:47.730
it wasn't taken seriously.

297
00:22:49.550 --> 00:22:54.410
As our searches for alien civilization turned out to be unfruitful,

298
00:22:54.410 --> 00:22:58.610
the Fermi paradox gained attention again,

299
00:22:58.610 --> 00:23:02.440
and it sparked more and more speculations.

300
00:23:02.440 --> 00:23:06.000
For example, the Rare Earth Hypothesis.

301
00:23:06.000 --> 00:23:10.130
It says aliens don't exist, that the earth is special.

302
00:23:10.130 --> 00:23:12.710
It's the only planet with intelligent life.

303
00:23:13.520 --> 00:23:17.960
Another hypothesis focuses on science and technology.

304
00:23:17.960 --> 00:23:21.240
It says aliens exist,

305
00:23:21.240 --> 00:23:26.550
but alien civilization is far more developed than human civilization,

306
00:23:26.550 --> 00:23:31.720
or far less developed than it, so they're unable to contact us.

307
00:23:31.720 --> 00:23:34.580
There's another one.

308
00:23:35.680 --> 00:23:38.540
It's about radio silence.

309
00:23:38.540 --> 00:23:40.960
I saw that as well.

310
00:23:40.960 --> 00:23:45.230
It says all aliens chose to keep silent.

311
00:23:46.350 --> 00:23:48.930
For some reason.

312
00:23:53.240 --> 00:23:58.610
There are many similar hypotheses.

313
00:23:58.610 --> 00:24:04.500
But none of them can verify whether alien civilization exists.

314
00:24:04.500 --> 00:24:08.830
Which one of those hypotheses
do you support?

315
00:24:11.060 --> 00:24:15.160
I've been doing scientific research for more than half of my life.

316
00:24:15.160 --> 00:24:21.040
I advocate thought experiments, but suspect everything.

317
00:24:24.720 --> 00:24:26.380
Wang,

318
00:24:27.200 --> 00:24:29.540
aren't you the same?

319
00:24:39.490 --> 00:24:44.270
Professor Ye didn't answer your question at all.

320
00:24:44.270 --> 00:24:45.510
She did.

321
00:24:45.510 --> 00:24:48.510
She said she advocated thought experiments but suspected everything.

322
00:24:48.510 --> 00:24:50.900
What's the matter? You find this answer unsatisfactory?

323
00:24:50.900 --> 00:24:53.640
Suspecting everything is an attitude.

324
00:24:53.640 --> 00:24:57.610
When you scientists do research, you have to pick a direction first, right?

325
00:24:57.610 --> 00:24:58.960
Take Newton for example.

326
00:24:58.960 --> 00:25:01.450
He believed light was a group of particles,

327
00:25:01.450 --> 00:25:04.540
but Huygens believed light was a wave,

328
00:25:04.540 --> 00:25:09.450
so they were both trying to prove their opinions in the directions they picked. Right?

329
00:25:11.060 --> 00:25:13.580
You know about the wave-particle duality?

330
00:25:13.580 --> 00:25:15.880
How can I not know it?

331
